# Auth0 Django Sample Environment File
#
# 1. Copy this file to '.env' (same directory) BEFORE running the server.
# 2. Replace the placeholder values on the right-hand side with the real
#    values from your Auth0 Application settings page.
# 3. Do NOT wrap values in braces { } and do NOT prefix the domain with https://
# 4. Allowed Callback URL (in Auth0 dashboard) should include:
#       http://localhost:3000/callback
#    Allowed Logout URL should include:
#       http://localhost:3000
# 5. After editing, restart the Django dev server so changes are loaded.
#
# If these are missing at runtime you'll see an error similar to:
#   ConnectionError: Failed to resolve 'none' /.well-known/openid-configuration
# which means AUTH0_DOMAIN (and likely the others) were not loaded.
############################################################

